Thorax . Pronotal ground punctation as on head; systematic punctures distinct, some coarse punctures loosely distributed between long arcuate row in anterior corner and densely arranged cluster in midlength of lateral margin. Elytral ground punctation as on head and pronotum; ten distinct rows of coarse punctures present; few coarse punctures distributed within interserial spaces, punctures in mesal rows distinctly finer, less strongly impressed, lateral rows completely unordered. Mesoventrite with distinct, low, semilunar, transversal projection, directed ventrad with two closely aggregated ridges not recognisable by 100× amplification (visible in SEM:
Minoshima et al . 2015
); long, narrow, low, median carina present posterior to transversal ridges, extending between metacoxae.

Distribution . Vietnam ( Vĩnh Phúc Prov.), China ( Yünnan ), Laos (Houa Phan Prov.:
Minoshima et al . 2015
).
